<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">251.11 Insull, Samuel/14:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Greece (<persName type="to">Morris</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-10T11:00:00-05:00">October 10, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>49. Your 107, October 10, 11 a.m. In view of fact that only remaining
                                formality necessary to bring extradition treaty in force between
                                United States and Greece is exchange of ratifications,<note n="18" xml:id="d389fn18">Treaty signed at Athens, May 6, 1931, <ref target="frus1931v02#pg_378">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1931, vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 378</ref>.</note>
                                Department directs you to request provisional arrest and detention
                                of Samuel Insull Senior with a view to his extradition on the
                                charges of embezzlement and larceny upon which warrants of arrest
                                have been issued in Cook County, Illinois.</p>
                            <p>Amount involved in embezzlement is over $200 and in larceny over
                                $25.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>